  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 450°F (230°C).",
    "Blanch poblanos in boiling water for 1 minute, then shock in ice water.",
    "Sauté minced garlic in olive oil until fragrant and slightly golden.",
    "Add red pepper flakes, lemon juice, salt, and pepper. Stir well.",
    "Remove poblano peppers from ice water and cut into strips.",
    "Mix Gouda cheese with tomato sauce; set aside.",
    "Combine Gouda-tomato sauce mixture with sautéed garlic-spice mixture.",
    "Add poblano strips to the sauce and stir-fry until heated through.",
    "Serve hot, as a side dish or dip."
